resources.name: Hey Prabhu!
resources.description:
An MX Player Original, Hey Prabhu is an Indian comedy-drama, directed by “Veere Di Wedding” fame Shashanka Ghosh. The show revolves around the millennial’s and what they go through in their everyday lives. It is a story of a common man Tarun Prabhu (Rajan Barmecha) and his unbelievable journey. Watch Hey Prabhu all episodes exclusively on MX Player.

The light-hearted show through its unique way looks at the values and ethics of the millennials. It also focuses on the problems faced by today’s youngsters in their real lives whether on a personal front or on a professional front. Watch Hey Prabhu online to see this slice-of-life comedy-drama.

resources.name: ImMature
resources.description:
ImMature is an Indian drama comedy web series by The Viral Fever. The 5 episode coming of age story depicts the life of a young boy Dhruv, who wants to grow up as soon as he can. Dhruv, with the help of his friends Kabir and Susu, tries to woo his first crush Chhavi, who is a class topper. Watch ImMature online to see this youth comedy-drama.

The series showcases the group of friends growing together as they have their first drink, have their first love, get their hearts broken, and much more. The show is all about the growing up phase and difficulties faced during the same. Watch ImMature all episodes to join the gang in their journey to youth.

resources.name: Aafat
resources.description:
Aafat is an Indian comedy-drama series which depicts the story of a young and handsome, Aakash. Aakash who is ready to get married is introduced to five different women as he aspires to find his perfect bride. Each of the five ladies though comes with her own unique characteristic which makes them imperfect in the eyes of the society. Catch Aafat online to witness this quirky comedy-drama.

Together the five ladies turn in to “Aafat” for Aakash. The show through its crisp story and unique concept is thought-provoking as well as hilarious. The show challenges the perception of an “ideal bride” in the eyes of society. Watch Aafat all episodes to see this blend of a different and unique take on arranged marriage.

resources.name: Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah
resources.description: Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah is a SAB Comedy Show inspired from the famous humorous column Duniya Ne Undha Chashmah written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This show revolves around Gada Family which consists of uneducated Businessman Jethalal Champaklal Gada (Actor Dilip Joshi), Jethalals Wife Daya (Disha Wakani) & their naughty Son Tipendra Gada (Bhavya Gandhi) living in Gokuldham Co-operative Society and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. In case of problem and emergency, Jethalal Gada often rushes to Taarak Mehta to seek his help and guidance as he finds a philosopher in him. Jethalal calls his Father Champaklal Gada (Amit Bhatt) from Village to keep an eye on his mischievous Son Tapu but the opposite happens and Bapuji joins hands with Tapu. This hilarious show will surely tickle your funny bone. Is there a trouble waiting for Jethalal?

resources.name: Jassi Jaissi Koi Nahin
resources.description: Jassi Jaisi Koi Nahin is a story of the lovable ugly duckling Jassis journey to becoming a beautiful swan and finding her prince charming. It is the story of Jasmeet Walia - Jassi - who is an unattractive, bespectacled girl with braces and an odd style of dressing. She is naive but intelligent. Jassi faces a lot of criticism from prettier colleagues - both men and women. The show chronicles her at her workplace where she wins the hearts of her colleagues and her boss due to her warm nature. Over time she falls in love with her boss, Armaan Suri. It is the story of Jassi whose life unfolds as she struggles to make a place for herself in the vain world and unite with the man she loves.
